Argument: Abolishing judicial activism would undermine the very foundations of our legal system. Judges are meant to interpret the law, not create policy. When they impose their personal beliefs, they disregard the will of the people and the legislative process. This erodes democratic principles and leads to unpredictable, inconsistent rulings. A system based on established law, not judicial overreach, is essential for stability and fairness.

